    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/1534371896604715/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 10924760,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 8029781,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8029781/dhaval-dalsania",
                "reputation": 1119,
                "display_name": "Dhaval Dalsania"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 113,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1553569720,
            "creation_date": 1495095427,
            "body": "<p>I think you have put command like <code>java -VERSION<\/code>. This is in capital letters\nYou need to put all command in lowercase letters<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>javac -version\njava -version\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>All characters must be in lowercase letter<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 44042224,
            "question_id": 37186197,
            "last_edit_date": 1553569720
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/411a68a53f54fe4d0b79d71da198e7ad?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 13960407,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 10081820,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10081820/saumya-agnihotri",
                "reputation": 904,
                "display_name": "Saumya Agnihotri"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 73,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1753897960,
            "creation_date": 1580068022,
            "body": "<p>I was facing a similar issue. Actually the command is :<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-bash prettyprint-override\"><code>java -version\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>and not<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-bash prettyprint-override\"><code>java --version\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>You will get output something like this:<\/p>\n<pre><code>java version &quot;1.8.0_162&quot;\nJava(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_162-b12)\nJava HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.162-b12, mixed mode)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 59922100,
            "question_id": 37186197,
            "last_edit_date": 1753897960
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Y28vX.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1790719,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1631197,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1631197/codingjeremy",
                "reputation": 5801,
                "display_name": "codingjeremy",
                "accept_rate": 83
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 73,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1613761637,
            "creation_date": 1613761637,
            "body": "<p>Java 8:<\/p>\n<pre><code>java -version\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>Java 9+:<\/p>\n<pre><code>java --version\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 66283618,
            "question_id": 37186197
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/885621564824877/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 7285378,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 6059495,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6059495/veli-mpinda",
                "reputation": 435,
                "display_name": "Veli Mpinda"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 31,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1510573437,
            "creation_date": 1510573437,
            "body": "<p>the command should be <strong>java -version<\/strong>                            <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 47263541,
            "question_id": 37186197
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/pX6ku.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1275953,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1231230,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1231230/ankur-singhal",
                "reputation": 26120,
                "display_name": "Ankur Singhal",
                "accept_rate": 76
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 13,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1463054730,
            "creation_date": 1463054730,
            "body": "<p>Try executing below command,<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>java -help\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>It gives option as, <\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>-version      print product version and exit<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p><strong>java -version<\/strong> is the correct command to execute<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 37186376,
            "question_id": 37186197
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ca8efdce20e50336bb83228a7ce21d5f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2201964,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1946145,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1946145/santosh-sindham",
                "reputation": 949,
                "display_name": "Santosh Sindham"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 12,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1571488228,
            "creation_date": 1571488228,
            "body": "<p><code>--version<\/code> is a valid option from JDK 9 and it is not a valid option until JDK 8 hence you get the below:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Unrecognized option: --version\nError: Could not create the Java Virtual Machine.\nError: A fatal exception has occurred. Program will exit.\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You can try installing JDK 9 or any version later and check for <code>java --version<\/code> it will work.<\/p>\n\n<p>Alternately, from the installed JDK 9 or later versions you can see from <code>java -help<\/code> the below two options will be available:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    -version      print product version to the error stream and exit\n    --version     print product version to the output stream and exit\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>where as in JDK 8 you will only have below when you execute <code>java -help<\/code><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    -version      print product version and exit\n\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I hope it answers your question.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 58463706,
            "question_id": 37186197
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-eDLkzgTV9qk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAbE/UGQdXpn7sOM/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 14986268,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 10818739,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10818739/jeremias-bila",
                "reputation": 121,
                "display_name": "Jeremias Bila"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 11,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1620730978,
            "creation_date": 1620730978,
            "body": "<p>This happens because the CMD doesn't recognize the &quot;java --version&quot; try writing &quot;java -version&quot;\nwhen &quot;java --version&quot; it tries to create a JVM. IT Fails because that's wrong command.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/DTf7W.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/DTf7W.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /><\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 67485461,
            "question_id": 37186197
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/kkBz6.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 12229185,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 8925790,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8925790/akash-perera",
                "reputation": 113,
                "display_name": "Akash Perera"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1510439735,
            "creation_date": 1510435974,
            "body": "<p>Your command is <strong>wrong<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n<p>Linux<\/p>\n\n<p><code>java -- version<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>macOS<\/p>\n\n<p><code>java -version<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>You can't use those commands other way around.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 47243004,
            "question_id": 37186197,
            "last_edit_date": 1510439735
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-vzeuyw25SYk/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAg/AlsIBjCpJiU/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
                "account_id": 13385273,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 9659378,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9659378/monti",
                "reputation": 814,
                "display_name": "monti"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1524039165,
            "creation_date": 1524039165,
            "body": "<pre><code>java -version\njava -showversion\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Both commands work In Linux 16.04 LTS<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 49894503,
            "question_id": 37186197
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9f10bffcb7d3a85d3ce628cebcad611b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 23481861,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 17533890,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/17533890/herion05",
                "reputation": 27,
                "display_name": "herion05"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1704926347,
            "creation_date": 1704926347,
            "body": "<p>As someone has pointed out before you get that error because <code>java --version<\/code> doesn't exist as a command before java 9+. I had a similar issue where I installed the latest version of jdk and the command would still return the exact same error you have provided. In my case the error came from having an older version of java still installed on my system.<\/p>\n<p>To fix this, since you're on Windows go to &quot;Settings&quot;-&gt;&quot;Apps &amp; Features&quot; and then search for &quot;Java&quot;. If you find that a you still have an older version of Java installed, particularly one before Java 9 like Java 8 for example, uninstall that version and install a newer version instead. Don't forget to configure the &quot;Environment Variables&quot; afterwards.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 77796772,
            "question_id": 37186197
        }
    ],
